article.headline: Pennsylvania 68, Dartmouth 44
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Tim Begley scored a game-high 14 points, including his career 1,000th, to lead Penn over Dartmouth 68-44 Saturday. Penn held Dartmouth (5-14, 2-4 Ivy League) to a season-low 25.9 percent from the floor. Begley came into the game with 991 points and became the 32nd player in Penn (11-7, 4-0) history to pass 1,000. Joining him in double figures were Mark Zoller with 12 points and Eric Osmundson with 11. Steve Danley had 10 rebounds. David Gardner and Steve Callahan each had 11 points for Dartmouth. Gardner also had eight rebounds.
